    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "An "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/skshader"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " object holds a custom OpenGL ES fragment shader. Shader objects are used to customize the drawing behavior of many different kinds of nodes in SpriteKit. "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "To use a custom shader, create an "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/skshader"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " object and provide the source for the custom fragment shader. If your shader needs to provide uniform data to the shader, create one or more "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/skuniform"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " objects and associate them with the shader object. If your shader needs to provide per-node data to the shader, create one or more "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/skattribute"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " objects and associate them with the relevant nodes. Then, assign the shader object to the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/skspritenode/1519714-shader"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property of any sprites that need the custom behavior. "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Compiling a shader and the uniform data associated with it can be expensive. Because of this, you should:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "unorderedList",
          "items": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Initialize shader objects when your game launches, not while the game is running."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Avoid changing the shaderâ€™s source or changing the list of uniforms or attributes while your game is running. Either of these things recompiles the shader."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Share shader objects whenever possible. If multiple sprites need the same behavior, create one shader object and associate it with every sprite that needs that behavior. Do not create a separate shader for each sprite."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "aside",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/skshader"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " does not support OpenGL Extensions. SpriteKit will return an error if you compile a project containing a fragment shader using extensions."
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "style": "important"
        }
      ]
    }
